PROFILE

C++ and Python developer with a BSc in Civil Aviation Management and a strong focus on AI architectures, algorithmic trading systems, complex systems simulation and signal processing.

Since 2019 I have been designing and implementing the CODE-21 / GODBRAIN ecosystem: a multi-agent, doctrine-driven architecture that combines evolutionary computation, behaviour-aware trading engines, parameterised universe simulations and frequency-based communication experiments.

I am now looking to formalise this work within the MSc Data Science and Computational Intelligence at Coventry University, and to develop it into rigorous, publishable research.
 
